com.github.crashdemons.playerheads.api

Interface HeadType

  • All Superinterfaces:
    HeadDisplay
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PHHeadType

    public interface HeadType
extends HeadDisplay
    Object representing the inbuilt PH type of Head supported by PlayerHeads. You can obtain the headtype for various things through API methods - to compare head types, you can use equals() This categorizes the head generally by entity type and does not retain user details (username/uuid/texture) - these valueus are defined instead by the specific type. If you want to tell if a head is the "same", you need to compare both type and owner (of the head itself), it is recommended to use HeadRepresentation for this purpose.
    Author:
    crashdemons (crashenator at gmail.com)

      • getOwner

        @NotNull
@NotNull UUID getOwner()
        Get the UUID associated with the skulltype (randomly assigned to it specifically). Note: this is NOT the player's UUID, it is a UUID assigned to the type.
        Returns:
        The UUID

      • isPlayerHead

        boolean isPlayerHead()
        Checks whether the skulltype uses a playerhead material internally. This indicates that either the skulltype is PLAYER or a mob without a vanilla head item, generally. Note: This does not necessarily indicate the material of the head - On certain server versions, even Player-Head items are variants of Skeleton skulls.
        Returns:
        true: the skulls is implemented using a playerhead. false: the skull has a different associated item
